response: "{ \"title\": \"Hard: Reverse Words in a String\", \"description\": \"Given an input string, reverse the order of words. Keep the same sequence of letters within each word.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef reverse_words(s: str) -> str:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `s` (str): A string containing one or more words separated by spaces.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns a string with the order of words reversed.\\n\", \"code\": \"def reverse_words(s: str) -> str:\\n    # Split the string into a list of words\\n    words = s.split()\\n    # Reverse the list and join it back into a string\\n    return ' '.join(words[::-1])\", \"tests\": [\"assert reverse_words(\\\"the sky is blue\\\") == \\\"blue is sky the\\\"\", \"assert reverse_words(\\\"hello world\\\") == \\\"world hello\\\"\", \"assert reverse_words(\\\"Python is fun\\\") == \\\"fun is Python\\\"\"] }"
